body:
Rivets Pt. 2

(Idk if I should put any tw’s on this part but I might edit that later)

‘From now on, you will be known as subject 0912. Nate is no longer your name. Is this understood or will we have to remind you again subject 0912?’ Dr. Lavrin snarled, sent in by the ring leader to dehumanize him. Nate would end up fighting tooth and nail, his genetics proved that already.

‘Sadly it looks like we’ll have to remind you,’ Nate started to brace himself, expecting the torment that came his way.

‘Ahhhh!’

‘I’m sorry but my name isn’t Subject whatever the fuck. It’s Nathan Smith.’

‘This wouldn’t be so difficult Subject 0912, if you just comply.’

Nate fighting to speak through the pain, screamed ‘NEVER’

‘Looks like the Subject is ready for the next phase.’

summary: Average views per an episode for each season of GMM
title: Average views per an episode for each season of GMM
body:
So the reason I have been more quiet than usual is that I’ve been averaging out the views of each episode or segment for each season. As you can imagine going through 2000+ videos is kinda of time consuming.

(See the bigger image here)
The first image is a breakdown just by season. As you can see, season 6 has the highest average of 5,310,017 views, with season 1 the lowest average of  1,000,895 views per an episode.
There was a significant dip for season’s 12 and 13 compared to to season 11. The reason for this is potentially the move to the GMM22 format.  At the end of the GMM22 we see a rise in views again for season 14, with season 15 also tracking upward in view average.

On seeing the basic season numbers, I decided for morbid curiosity to bring Good Mythical Summer into play, as well as splitting season 12 into pre GMM22 and GMM22, and well it got interesting.

(See the bigger image here)
Good Mythical Summer #1 had a better view average than season 11 (3,718,348 views compared to 3,181,049 views). Season 12 prior to the move to multiple segments also tracked an average of over 3 million views per an episode. The introduction of GMM 22 saw the average dropped to  1,121,410 views per a segment. After dropping one segment for season 13, the average views went up to 1,655,420.
With the return to the traditional format for Good Mythical Summer 2, views again went up to 2,058,252 views per an episode.
